<subSubSection id="C37CB1CFFFDAFFED55EDFEF54FAEB708" pageId="3" pageNumber="381" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD9E244FFDAFFED55EDFEF54FAEB708" blockId="3.[151,1437,311,591]" pageId="3" pageNumber="381">
<emphasis id="B9123E56FFDAFFED55EDFEF54C31B414" bold="true" box="[151,274,311,338]" pageId="3" pageNumber="381">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This genus is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C6699C7FFDAFFED5749FEFA4F86B414" authorityName="Mulsant &amp; Rey" authorityYear="1855" box="[563,677,312,338]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Stegelytra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="381" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9123E56FFDAFFED5749FEFA4F86B414" box="[563,677,312,338]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="381">Stegelytra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6699C7FFDAFFED579AFEFA4E7FB414" authorityName="Wei &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2010" box="[736,860,312,338]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Honguchia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="381" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9123E56FFDAFFED579AFEFA4E7FB414" box="[736,860,312,338]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="381">Honguchia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having reticulate forewing venation and lateral frontal sutures extending to corresponding ocellus, but differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C6699C7FFDAFFED56E1FE9E492EB430" authorityName="Mulsant &amp; Rey" authorityYear="1855" box="[923,1037,348,374]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Stegelytra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="381" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9123E56FFDAFFED56E1FE9E492EB430" box="[923,1037,348,374]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="381">Stegelytra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by: (i) forewing apex truncate; (ii) the anteclypeus broad and convex with latero-apical areas depressed, lora very narrow; (iii) pronotum with lateral carina straight and the posterior margin sinuate; (iv) scutellum without median or posterolateral ridge or keel; (v) valve fused with the subgenital plate; (vi) paramere very elongate and by the apically fimbriolate aedeagus. And it also differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C6699C7FFDAFFED5423FE2E4CF6B740" authorityName="Wei &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2010" box="[345,469,492,518]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Honguchia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="381" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9123E56FFDAFFED5423FE2E4CF6B740" box="[345,469,492,518]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="381">Honguchia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by: (i) the lateral margin of the postclypeus more strongly convex, apical veins of the forewing modified but not reticulate; (ii) the unusual triangular shaped basal lobe of the subgenital plate projecting into the pygofer; (iii) the styles much longer.
</paragraph>
